Global Peripheral Intravascular Ultrasound (IVUS) Catheter Market Insights
Peripheral Intravascular Ultrasound (IVUS) Catheter Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.6 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Peripheral Intravascular Ultrasound (IVUS) Catheter Market Overview
The global Peripheral Intravascular Ultrasound (IVUS) Catheter Market was valued at USD 450 million in 2024, and is projected to reach USD 830 million by 2030, with a CAGR of 12.6%. The increasing adoption of minimally invasive procedures, technological advancements, and rising demand for advanced diagnostic tools in cardiovascular diseases are driving the growth of this market. The introduction of next-generation IVUS catheters with improved imaging capabilities and the need for enhanced clinical outcomes are further contributing to the market expansion. The market's growth is also supported by rising awareness about peripheral arterial diseases (PAD) and growing healthcare expenditure across various regions.

